{"name": "env-cache", "metadata": {"name": "env-cache", "version": "0.2", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Get a Python environment for a Python version and requirements.txt file", "upload_time": 1733492454}, "documentation": ["Get a Python environment for a Python version and requirements.txt file\n\n`env_cache` manages a collection of Python environments. You request an\nenvironment for a specific Python version and a set of requirements (preferably\nwith pinned versions, like from `pip freeze`). It can either create a new\nenvironment with these packages, or retrieve one it already made with the same\narguments.\n\nTo get different versions of Python, `env_cache` can use\n[pyenv](https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv), [conda](https://docs.conda.io/en/latest/),\nor [spack](https://spack.io/). It can also work with a single 'fixed' Python\ninterpreter to create virtualenvs - in this case, only one Python version is\navailable.\n\nUsage (with pyenv):\n\n```python\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom env_cache import PyenvEnvMaker, EnvsManager\n\nif len(sys.argv) != 3:\n    sys.exit(\"Usage: eg-pyenv.py 3.8.11 path/to/requirements.txt\")\n\npy_version, reqs_path = sys.argv[1:]\nreqs = Path(reqs_path).read_text('utf-8')\n\nenvmgr = EnvsManager(Path('my-envs'), PyenvEnvMaker())\nenv_dir = envmgr.get_env(py_version, reqs)\n```\n\nIt returns a [pathlib](https://docs.python.org/3/library/pathlib.html) Path\nobject (`env_dir` above) pointing to the environment directory. Python can\nbe run from `bin/python` within this directory.\n\nIt also records each time an environment is requested in a crude `usage.csv`\nfile in the environment directory. This is meant to help with cleaning up\nunused environments, but it may go away or change completely in a future version.\n\nThis package is written primarily for internal use at [European XFEL](https://www.xfel.eu/), so it's fairly rough, and we might make breaking\nchanges without warning.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "env_cache", "documentation": ["Get a Python environment for a Python version and requirements.txt file"], "functions": [{"name": "env_cache.usage_record", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Make one row for usage.csv"]}], "variables": [{"name": "env_cache.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "env_cache.reqs_txt", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "env_cache.fixed_py", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "env_cache.EnvMaker", "bases": ["abc.ABC"], "methods": [{"name": "env_cache.EnvMaker.describe", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "py_version", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Make a description of this Python version, to go in requirements.txt"]}, {"name": "env_cache.EnvMaker.make_env", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "env_dir", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "py_version", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a new environment with the given Python version"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "env_cache.FixedPythonEnvMaker", "bases": ["EnvMaker"], "methods": [{"name": "env_cache.FixedPythonEnvMaker.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "python_exe", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "env_cache.FixedPythonEnvMaker._get_version", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "env_cache.FixedPythonEnvMaker._check_version", "